@271  = ~  Bruenor Battlehammer is an angry dwarf leader from Icewind Dale. He adopted and saved a young human girl, Catti-Brie, who had lost her parents in a attack of some group of thieves and gave a home to the dark elf Drizzt Do'Urden. After a victorious battle against barbarians, he spared the life of one young barbarian on the condition to serve him for five years. The barbarian was called Wulfgar.
  During the years they all became friends with each other, Drizzt, Bruenor and Wulfgar. Catti-Brie and Wulfgar became lovers. After the five years Bruenor forged a war hammer Aegis Fang as a gift for Wulfgar and as the boy was in love with Catti-Brie, he didn't leave.
  One day Bruenor's friend Regis came to seek hospitality without explanations. Bruenor of course welcomed the halfling and the five of them played a big role in freeing the Icewind Dale from the Crystal Shard. After that he led them all on a quest to take back the legendary Mithril Hall from Druegars.
  Inside they met the true conqueror of the Hall, a black dragon. Bruenor killed it, but fell into a ravine with it. He survived. When the dragon died dwarves took over Mithril Hall and Bruenor became the king.
  Some time later in a drow attack to the Mithril Hall the first king of the Battlehammers Clan escaped from his eternal prison in the drow city of Menzoberranzan and arranged a pretty big surprise by suddenly coming alive after hundreds of years. After the worst shock Bruenor entrusted the clan's leadership back into the first one's hands, gaining in return the freedom to travel along with his friends.
  Bruenor is very stubborn, steadfast and hot-headed dwarf who slays enemies with his axe. Although his is tough from the outside, he has a warm heart. Still, it is not recommended to face him in a duel.~
