@674  = ~When asked about his past, Mordragon's face darkens and he begins his tale. About two years ago all was well. He was reaching paladinhood, was in love with a local lady and could not have been happier. Their love blossomed and wedding was near. But then a plague struck and by cruel faith Mordragon was the sole survivor of his family. That being bad enough already, the plague also claimed the life of his lover. Mordragon felt quilty of being alive and grieved for his losses but could not find any comfort in anything. He ran to the mountains to find himself but the old Mordragon was gone, for good. Everything had been taken from him and he became angry. Angry at the world, angry at everyone. Why should there be happiness while he was in pain? Caring about nothing anymore he made his way through the dales and woods with no purpose. His whereabouts of the past few months are unknown even to himself.~
