@737  = ~  When asked about his past Randall seems to stare at you blankly, and you suddenly have the feeling that he is a very sad person. After a few seconds he begins his tale in a somewhat quivering voice...
  As a child he was abandoned by his true parents in the woods, left there alone to suffer an almost certain death by the cruel hands of nature. Up to this day he doesn't know why he was abandoned, but he thinks the reason is a simple cruel one: he is an half-elf, the fruit of a forbidden love.
  Be it by chance or by fate, he was rescued by Fiona, the wife of a rich merchant from the city of Athkatla who went by the name of Marcus Von' Licnor. Fiona and Marcus had been trying to have a child of their own for quite some time, but had been unsuccessful. When most priests told them it would be impossible, they prayed to Thorm for his help and guidance. Thorm answered, or at least that's what Fiona reasoned, by sending them this half-elven child to raise as their own. So, they kept the child and named him Randall.
  Randall's first years were pretty uneventful and even quite happy. He was surrounded by love and affection, and the fact that he was a half-breed and both his parents human never seemed to bother him too much.
  When he started showing certain affinity with the magical arts, Marcus revealed a deep secret to him: In his youth he had been a necromancer of considerable power and one of Bhaal's most fervent followers...But then something had happened. In his dreams the mighty lion-headed god Thorm had visited him, and he had seen the light... He had decided to escape and start a new life in Athkatla...
  Under Marcus's wise tutelage Randall began dominating the complexities of spell casting and magic writing, becoming quite a competent magician.
  When Randall reached the age of seventeen life suddenly turned dark for him...
  His father was attacked by a small group of Cyric followers who wished to gain their god's favour, and though he was able to escape almost unharmed, he was taken prisoner by the Cowled Wizards, never to be heard of again.
  Fiona crumbled after having lost her loving husband and been humiliated by the discovery of his evil past...After various months of depression and moaning she finally committed suicide by stabbing herself to death with a dagger...
  Randall was once again left all alone in the world, and finding no better solution, he decided to abandon the city he had learnt to call home and travel the road in search for answers...or at least in a search for a way to ease his pain...~
