@780  = ~  The halfling Regis comes from the cruel city of Calimport. He's a coward and a little fat and lazy and rather eats good food in a soft chair than kills monsters threatening his life. His position in Calimport was a servant, servant of Pasha Pook. Because of his greed he craved an amulet of his own master and eventually stole it.
  He knew if he'd stay in Calimport, he'd be a dead man in no time...So, he fled to Icewind Dale, seeking protection from his friend, Bruenor Battlehammer.
  Surprisingly he became the hero of the dale by destroying a Crystal Tower (actually it was Drizzt who deserved the honor). Regis was served like a king, but captured one day without no-one knowing that.
  Pasha Pook had sent an assassin, Artemis Enteri, after him. When Regis was being dragged back to Calimport, the assassin took his form with an illusion and travelled with his companions to the Mithril Hall.
  When the illusion faded, Drizzt, Wulfgar, Bruenor and Catti-Brie stormed to Calimport as fast as they could and freed him.
  In the world Regis is known as one of the five companions. Coward he might be, but gutsy too. He is also a pretty good thief. Small as he is, it is easy for him to sneak around unnoticed.~
