@910  = ~  Wulfgar, the great and powerful barbarian tribe leader, now travelling with his friends Bruenor, Catti-Brie, Regis and Drizzt.
  Wulfgar has incredible strength and with his war hammer Aegis Fang (a magical hammer, forged by Bruenor Battlehammer as a gift) he is aknowledged as a very fearsome foe for anyone. He is the "servant" of the barbarian god Tempus and when you hear his battle cry, you want to run, fast.
  Wulfgar grew up in a barbarian tribe and was with a group who attacked against the dwarves living in Icewind Dale. The barbarians were defeated and in order to stay alive he had to serve Bruenor Battlehammer, a dwarven leader, for five years and in that time they became friends.
  With the help of the drow ranger Drizzt Do'Urden, Bruenor trained Wulfgar to be a man. He fell in love with Catti-Brie, a human who lived amongst the dwarves as Bruenor's adoptive daughter and when the five years had gone, Wulfgar decided to stay.
  Unfortunately his romantic affairs with Catti-Brie ended when he "fell". Everybody thought he died in a battle against powerful creatures from underground but actually he was drawn into the hell where the great demon Errtu tortured him for six long years until he was finally freed with the help of his companions.
  Wulfgar couldn't stand the horrors of the past and parted from his friends again. Soon after he started drinking and for a long time he kept the memories away with alcohol. But then something happened that put him face to face with the horrors of the past and the strong barbarian was able to overcome them.
  He returned to his companions with a wife and a child (though the child was not his). Catti-Brie and Drizzt had a deep relationship, which surprisingly didn't anger him. He was aware that what he had had with Catti-Brie would never be again.~
